                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Data for He-6."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "2UK EDG"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ". Department of physics."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Cf-252 source, 1mm diameter, emitting 850",
                " pulses per second. It was a thin and uniform",
                " deposit mounted flush with the surface of the",
                " cathode in the scintillation cell. It was deposited",
                " onto a Ni-foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "   Use of a E-dE detector to identify the",
                " light particles emitted in the fission."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A coincidence is required between these",
                " light particles and the output of the fission",
                " detector to select ternary fission events."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COIN",
                "PROPC",
                "TELES"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The fission fragments are detected",
                " in a xenon filled proportional scintillator. It",
                " was filled with xenon at a pressure of 760 torr.",
                " The distance between cathode and anode mesh was 15",
                " mm. The amplitude of the photomultiplier pulse",
                " gave the energy of the fragment. The fall time",
                " of the photomultiplier pulse between 90. And 10%",
                " pulse height yielded the angle of the fission",
                " fragment. The corresponding charged light particles",
                " are identified in coincidence in a telescope",
                " arrangement of two solid state detectors.",
                " The emission angles of the other particles involved",
                " are calculated using conservation of momentum.",
                " The detectors are calibrated with alpha lines from",
                " Pu-239,Am-241,Cm-244."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".A Gaussian shape was fitted to the light particle",
                " energy distribution. This is due to 13.5 MeV",
                " discrimination level for the alpha particles.",
                " The deviation from the Gaussian shape at lower",
                " energies is therefore not seen."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Energy losses of the fission fragments in the",
                " xenon gas of the detector and in the nickel foil",
                " backing they go through."
              ]
            }
          ],
